  "prompt": "Why should I tip my server?",
  "response": "There are several reasons to tip servers:\n\n1. Income structure\n- Many servers are paid below minimum wage\n- Tips make up a significant portion of their total earnings\n- Their base wage often doesn't cover living expenses\n\n2. Service quality\n- Tipping acknowledges good service\n- Encourages servers to provide attentive and professional service\n- Rewards hard work and customer care\n\n3. Social custom\n- Tipping is a standard practice in many countries\n- It's considered polite and expected in most restaurants\n\n4. Supporting workers\n- Servers often have physically demanding jobs\n- Many rely on tips to support themselves and their families\n\n5. Compensation for effort\n- Servers handle multiple tasks simultaneously\n- They manage customer interactions, food preparation, and table service\n- Tips recognize the complexity of their work\n\nTypical tip amounts range from 15-20% of the total bill, depending on service quality and local customs.",
